    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About Juicebox\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\nAbout the role\n\nWe're looking to add a strong senior IC who can take over major parts of the codebase and help maintain technical velocity as we scale. This person will work closely with the founders, act as a high-trust reviewer, and raise the bar for engineering quality and speed. You’ll shape architectural decisions and mentor teammates — without needing to manage people. Perfect for someone who wants autonomy, impact, and to be part of a tight, flat org shipping fast.\n\nWhat we’re looking for (technical)\n\n - You have hands-on experience building features / leading projects from scratch\n\n - You have a deep understanding of systems and infrastructure\n\n - You have experience with JS frameworks and full-stack web apps\n\n - You’ve been in fast-paced startup environments\n\nWhat we’re looking for (non technical)\n\n - You’re good at (1) learning things quickly and (2) getting things done.\n\n - You've shown excellence: be it in your education, work experiences, projects, or anything else you can share.\n\n - You’re good at communication and enjoy working in person.\n\nNice to haves\n\n - You were / want to be a founder.\n\n - You have experience with large-scale data pipelines or search clusters.\n\nCompensation \u0026 Benefits\n\n - Medical, dental, vision\n\n - Lunch stipend\n\n - Office in downtown San Francisco",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
